Note that in Fig. 2, Loss2, reflecting the IR condition,
remains 00 throughout the whole training process. The training LOSS is
dominated by Loss3, which is high at the begining and approaches 00 later.
This means that WBB is satisfied by the trained network except for some rare
cases. For example, in Table 2, except for the
rare case where the cost types of all data owners exceed a threshold (with
a prior probability less than 10âˆ’2superscript10210^{-2}), Loss3 is 00. On the other hand,
Loss1, the unfairness level, remains positive. This is because by definition
the unfairness function being 00 implies a linear payment structure, which
cannot satisfy IR and WBB.
